Tom:<br>
You are a special man to have as much compassion as you do for your fellow human beings.  Some are more saintly than you.. others are at the far opposite end of the continumm.  Most oscilate somewhere to the left and right of center.<br>
If you can forgive those who spit or pee on one another.. surely you can find some tolerance for those who react with anger at being spit at.<br>
You're smart enough to know that two wrongs don't make a right.  I'm not saying that it is right to kick the shit out of someone who spits at you.. or spit back or turn the other cheek.  Different times, circumstances, moods etc. would impact upon how I would respond.  Automated thought tells me that I would react with violence.  Spitting on someone is not a violent act in itself.. but it is certainly a provocative one.<br>
Often people choose to emulate excellent behavior (such as yours) rather than respond favorably to confrontation and chastizement( Oops!..such as yours.)<br>
If I had a magic wand.. I would make you perfect like me.<br>
